=== One-sample

Tests if the mean of a single sample differs from a known or hypothesized population mean.

$
t = (overline(x) - mu_0) / (s / sqrt(n))
$

- $overline(x)$: sample mean
- $mu_0$: hypothesized population mean
- $s$: sample standard deviation
- $n$: sample size

